%I A396317 #82 Jul 12 2026 20:46:24
%S A396317 0,0,0,0,246,4150,31500,155820,586040,1818936,4895100,11797500,
%T A396317 26037990,53483430,103479376,190335600,335244000,568705760,933550920,
%U A396317 1488639816,2313342150,3512895750,5224753380,7626032260,10942187256,15457035000,21524262500,29580560100
%N A396317 Number of n X n binary matrices with exactly 8 1's such that there are an even number of 1's in every row and column.
%C A396317 Also weight A_8 of the Weight Distribution for a square n X n Single Parity Check Product (SPCP) code when the 1's represent bit errors, and 0's represent unchanged data bits. For SPCP code, A_odd = 0, A_4 = C(n,2)^2 = A000537(n-1), A_6 = 3!*C(n,3)^2 = A179058(n). See the rectangular formula for other message data formats.
%D A396317 E. R. Berlekamp, Algebraic Coding Theory, McGraw-Hill, New York, 1968, pp. 397-400.
%D A396317 R. E. Blahut, Theory and Practice of Error Control Codes, Addison-Wesley, 1983, p. 431.
%D A396317 C. Leung, Evaluation of the Error Probability of Single Parity-Check Codes, IEEE Transactions on Communications Vol. COM-31, NO. 2, Feb 1983, pp. 250-253.
%D A396317 F. J. MacWilliams, and N. J. A. Sloane The Theory of Error Correcting Codes, Elsevier/North Holland 1977, p. 21.
%D A396317 W. W. Peterson, and E. J. Weldon, Error Correcting Codes, MIT Press, 1994, pp. 64-70, pp. 131-132.
%H A396317 G. Gordon Thompson, <a href="/A396317/b396317.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..100</a>
%H A396317 A. M. Patel, <a href="https://mirrors.meulie.net/bitsavers.org/pdf/ibm/IBM_Journal_of_Research_and_Development/186/ibmrd1806Q.pdf">Optimal Rectangular Code for High Density Magnetic Tapes</a>
%H A396317 G. Gordon Thompson, <a href="/A396317/a396317_2.pdf">Probability of Undetected Error for Some Simple Product Codes</a>, MS Thesis, UT Arlington TX, May 1984, pp. 35-37.
%H A396317 <a href="/index/Rec#order_09">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (9,-36,84,-126,126,-84,36,-9,1).
%F A396317 a(n) = 90*C(n,4)^2 + 36*C(n,4)*C(n,3) + 2*C(n,2)*C(n,4).
%F A396317 a(n) = (1/96)*n^2*(n - 1)^2*(n - 2)*(n - 3)*(15*n^2 - 51*n + 46).
%F A396317 The rectangular formula for n X k matrices is a(n,k) = 90*C(n,4)* C(k,4) + 18*C(n,4)*C(k,3) + 18*C(n,3)*C(k,4) + C(n,2)*C(k,4) + C(n,4)*C(k,2).
%F A396317 G.f.: -2*x^4*(28*x^4+528*x^3+1503*x^2+968*x+123)/(x-1)^9. - _Alois P. Heinz_, May 30 2026
%F A396317 E.g.f.: exp(x)*x^4*(984 + 2336*x + 1372*x^2 + 264*x^3 + 15*x^4)/96. - _Stefano Spezia_, Jun 24 2026
%e A396317 The first formula given above adds the counts of 3 subsets that are categorized by the number of 1's in rows and columns (with transpositions in the same category).
%e A396317 For n = 4, a(4) = 90*1 + 36*4 + 2*6 = 246 by the formula. See also the figures below, showing an example for each subset:
%e A396317 .
%e A396317 Subset 1 - exactly 2 1's per row and 2 1's per column.
%e A396317 1 1 0 0
%e A396317 1 0 1 0     The number of patterns of 2 1's per row and column is
%e A396317 0 1 0 1     90, see A001499(4).
%e A396317 0 0 1 1
%e A396317 .
%e A396317 Subset 2 - 1 row or 1 column of 4 1's, otherwise 0 or 2 per row/column.
%e A396317             Initially we consider 4 1's in a row:
%e A396317 1 1 1 1      - 18 patterns of 1's for the nonzero rows;
%e A396317 1 1 0 0      - 4 ways to choose 3 rows to be nonzero.
%e A396317 0 0 1 1     Finally, a doubling of choices comes from transposition.
%e A396317 0 0 0 0       Total choices 18*4*2 = 144.
%e A396317 .
%e A396317 Subset 3 - 2 rows or 2 columns of 4 1's.
%e A396317             Initially we consider 4 1's in 2 rows:
%e A396317 1 1 1 1      - only 1 pattern of 1's for the nonzero rows;
%e A396317 1 1 1 1      - 6 ways to choose 2 rows to be nonzero.
%e A396317 0 0 0 0     Finally, a doubling of choices comes from transposition.
%e A396317 0 0 0 0       Total choices 1*6*2 = 12.
%e A396317 .
%e A396317 For n = 5, a(5) = 90*25 + 36*50 + 2*50 = 4150.
%t A396317 A396317[n_] := n^2*(n - 3)*(n - 2)*(n - 1)^2*(3*n*(5*n - 17) + 46)/96;
%t A396317 Array[A396317, 30, 0] (* _Paolo Xausa_, Jun 24 2026 *)
%Y A396317 Cf. A001499, A000537, A179058, A179063, A396321.
%K A396317 nonn,easy,changed
%O A396317 0,5
%A A396317 _G. Gordon Thompson_, May 21 2026
